<br>
I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>love</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> making <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rods of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on raids.  Its speeds up the preparation for the encounter immensely, helps enormously when there are wipeouts, and allows my guild to do more with an odd mix of classess.  Makes the entire raid team more powerful than they would be without them.<br>
<br>
Having a mage group on a raid helps enormously.  With three or more mages, rods are hardly a noticeable duty, even when they are in great demand.  I help other mages exp and work on epic bits, so even when the guild is short on mages, it's simply a matter of getting on the Xev magician channel and getting a couple more mages from smaller guilds to join the raid.  They are usually eager to go on raids that their guild can't yet handle, and are happy to share the work.  For the younger mages that can't yet drop T-Rods, they can handle all the requests for focus gear, etc.<br>
<br>
Another thing I've found that helps is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  pet cannibalization</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I can dump my entire mana bar in rods, and be back to full mana again in under two minutes without any attention from a healer.  This is best during the preparation stage, as it deprives you of a fighting pet.<br>
<br>
One nice thing to do with the mage group is to assign one  to each enchanter to assist.  Anything the chanter targets for mezz, the mages assists and cast malosini or whatever.  This is especially helpful when we are training younger enchanters who have a harder time landing spells on the mob.<br>
<br>
There is no good reason for any mage to suffer because of rod duty.  The more mages, the merrier mages are.  Nothing like the mage group destroying an add with pets, and druids, which I am blessed with an excess of, make fine healers for the mage group.<br>
<br>
Sure, being the only mage on a raid to make rods would probably suck pretty bad.  But that's not how we do things.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Ancient Fellowship, Xev</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
